\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 SimpleComboBox is a little document based application which shows how to use a Cocoa NSComboBox.  The application allows user to edit and save information about music CDs.  Among other things, the document contains a combo box which allows users to specify the music genre.  This sample code demonstrates:\
\
	\'a5 How to populate an NSComboBox using data source methods.\
	\'a5 How to implement auto completion for a combo box.\
	\'a5 An implementation of undo/redo for parts of a document that don't automatically provide undo.\
	\'a5 Archiving and unarchiving a simple document format.\
