\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 CDInfoDocument is our document controller, and a subclass of 
\f0\b NSDocument
\f1\b0 .  Along with managing the basics of the document (saving, opening), CDInfoDocument also controls the 
\f0\b genreComboBox
\f1\b0 , as it's data source.  The data source method 
\f0\b numberOfItemsInComboBox:
\f1\b0 , returns the number of entries the combo box has in it  and 
\f0\b comboBox:objectValueForItemAtIndex: 
\f1\b0 supplies the string to be displayed in a given row.  CDInfoDocument implements 
\f0\b comboBox:completedString: 
\f1\b0 to allow the genre combo box to auto complete much like a web browsers address field.  Finally, CDInfoDocument provides undo/redo for the text fields by registering for 
\f0\b NSControlTextDidBeginEditingNotification
\f1\b0 , and 
\f0\b NSControlTextDidEndEditingNotification
\f1\b0  for the combo box and other text fields (band name, cd title).  The notifications are received when the user ends editing one of the text fields or combo box, and not on each key stroke.  So undo/redo for these fields will not be per key stroke.\
